<p><b>Is The Longest Ride worth reading?</b> The Longest Ride is a captivating and emotional story that is definitely worth reading. It explores the complexities of love and the power of fate.</p>
<p><b>What is the longest book ever?</b> A la recherche du temps perdu by Marcel Proust contains an estimated 9,609,000 characters (each letter counts as one character. Spaces are also counted, as one character each). The title translates to "Remembrance of Things Past".</p>
<p><b>Do Ruth and Ira adopt Daniel?</b> Ruth was a school teacher who became very attached to a young boy in her class. Because he comes from a broken family, her and Ira begin taking him in as their own and, eventually, Ruth decides she wanted to adopt him but his guardians wouldn't allow it.</p>
